tar-boy
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a shed-hand who applies tar to a cut on a sheep being shorn.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: shearing; aka tarboy, tar boy
